Yes, you can convert an integer to a string in C# using several methods. One of the most common ways to do this is by using the `ToString()` method. Here's a simple example:

```csharp
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        int number = 123;

        // Convert integer to string using ToString() method
        string numberAsString = number.ToString();

        Console.WriteLine("The number as a string is: " + numberAsString);
    }
}
```

In this example, the `ToString()` method is called on the integer `number` to convert it to a string. The result is stored in `numberAsString` and printed to the console. This is a straightforward and commonly used method to perform this conversion in C#.
